Ga$_{2}$O$_{3}$ exhibits a variety of structures: \begin{itemize} \item $\alpha$Ga$_{2}$O$_{3}$, which has the \href{current_web_home_dir/A2B3_hR10_167_c_e-001}{corundum ($D5_{1}$) structure}, \item $\beta$Ga$_{2}$O$_{3}$ (this structure), \item \href{current_web_home_dir/A11B4_cF120_227_acdf_e-001}{$\gamma$Ga$_{2}$O$_{3}$}, and \item $\epsilon$Ga$_{2}$O$_{3}$, a structure with many vacancies which can be approximated by the \href{current_web_home_dir/A2B3_oP40_33_4a_6a-001}{$\kappa$ alumina structure}. \end{itemize} ~ \vspace{-.25in} 
 There are numerous structures with the AFLOW prototype label A2B3\_mC20\_12\_2i\_3i or A3B2\_mC20\_12\_3i\_2i.  They are generated by the same symmetry operations with different sets of parameters ({\tt --params}) specified in their corresponding CIF files. 
 We have identified the following structures as sufficiently different to warrant their own prototypes: \begin{itemize} \item Prototypes with the label A2B3\_mC20\_12\_2i\_3i: \begin{itemize} \item \href{current_web_home_dir/A2B3_mC20_12_2i_3i-001}{$\beta$-Ga$_{2}$O$_{3}$} (this structure) \item \href{current_web_home_dir/A2B3_mC20_12_2i_3i-003}{$\alpha$-As$_{2}$Te$_{3}$} \end{itemize} ~ \vspace{-.25in} \item Prototypes with the label A3B2\_mC20\_12\_3i\_2i: \begin{itemize} \item \href{current_web_home_dir/A3B2_mC20_12_3i_2i-001}{Mo$_{2}$As$_{3}$} \item \href{current_web_home_dir/A3B2_mC20_12_3i_2i-002}{Gd$_{2}$Cl$_{3}$} \end{itemize} \end{itemize}
